                    <msContents>
                        <summary>A woodblock printed work by Ishida Teikan on childhood diseases and their treatment in hiragana-majiri script, and published by a pharmacist of Kyoto named Ishida Kenji who appears to have some connection with the author as the patent medicines produced by the pharmacy are recommended by the author. According to an end note the work was originally published in 1813 but this is a copy of a new edition published in 1851 with further revisions and additions made in 1859. Other impressions or editions are recorded for 1862, 1865, 1870 and 1874. The book also contains a portrait of the author at the age of 95.
                            
                        </summary>

